We need to rethink in this new age whether NDP is still relevant in creating “a stronger Singapore”? How does organising NDP, costing more tax payers money,  going to lead us out of the economy fallout that is about to come?

answers.text: @eat_till_bui I think it's about coming together as one

@eat_till_bui i suppose the experts that is fighting for Singapore's economy have given some thoughts on this problem of yours already. There definitely are hidden/potential benefit having a NDP will bring. Like some people have mentioned, it will provide rent money for many people. Preparations takes month so those month of working can help a lot. These kind of this is usually a display of strength, afterall, that is the purpose of performance such as these. Having a strong image can go very far. This different edition of NDP will reduce the cost on some aspect as well so it wouldnt be a strain to our economy.
@eat_till_bui if everything is about money, you will see us opening everything immediately. It’s called a balance between various factors

@xinnix_lee unfortunately this is Sg, everything is money. If merely as symbolic then I have nothing else to debate :) Our art industry is actually been oppressed to be frank, but this is for another debate. 😂
@yuharnshin you are right to say that national patriotism is all time low now, I still have a different view on this but it’s always good to debate and share views 👍

@eat_till_bui that’s why it’s scaled down isn’t it ? NDP is not a solution to help us out of the economy fall out. It was never meant to be a solution. It is more of a symbol . Not everything is just about money. There’s a reason why arts industry exist
@xinnix_lee then all other events that affect the livelihoods shl also proceed or scale down also isn’t it?
@eat_till_bui that’s like saying there shouldn’t be any celebration at all to save money. Events help to provide jobs for people.

@eat_till_bui the numbers may not be significant, but to the people involved it would. As for the impression, it isn't for the world, its for us. What do singaporeans feel when they see articles like this? The nationwide hype and patriotism NDP usually triggers is now diminished. While downscaling NDP may be the wise choice, it is at the expense of all these.

@yuharnshin Only a small percentage of employment will result from NDP, like how many event coys can NDP give work to? So need to see the overall employment created vs total expenses to see if worth it. As for negative image, we are in the mist of a global pandemic that was not seen since 1918, every country is fighting their own war, so I don’t think cancelling/downsizing our little NDP will make the whole world look badly at SG. 👍

@eat_till_bui NDP is a major national event, won't cancelling or downscaling it have a negative impression? As for employment, the workers have to work for weeks or months to prepare everything, while they may be insignificant figures, but every bit of work is crucial especially when you're struggling financially. This is imo tho, data mite prove me wrong
@yuharnshin that’s a valid point
@eat_till_bui not to mention the job opportunities, though temporary, a large scale NDP will create
@eat_till_bui it's to create an image. If there's a global recession, having a showy NDP will publicly display that sg has the means to pull thru tough times
